                                 <locus from="31r" to="38v"/>
                                  VII(8; s.l.: 6, no stub; 7, stub after
                                 7/fols. 31r-38v)
 
 </item>
                              <note>ff. 1-4 (quire I), fols. 7-8 in quire
                                 II, <locus from="24" to="25">fols. 24-25</locus> in quire VI, placed loosely, originate from a
                                 different manuscript.</note>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The sewing is missing. Many folios are probably
                           missing, some are misplaced. Some fols. originating from a different Ms.
                           (also a lectionary, dating approximately to the same time): fols. 1-4
                           (quire I, incipit of <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>), and fols. 7-8,
                           24-25 (loosely placed into the respective quires). 
 A tear carefully
                           amended in <locus target="#32">32</locus>.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     
                  </objectDesc>
                  
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Readings are indicated by the names of the feasts
                              and liturgical periods, framed, written in the upper margin in the
                              main hand: ዘጻድቃን: <locus target="#1r">fol. 1r</locus> (hand b).
                              ዘመላእክት: <locus target="#8r">fol. 8r</locus> (hand b). ዘልደት: <locus target="#9r">fol. 9r</locus> (hand a). &lt;...&gt;: <locus target="#12r">fol. 12r</locus>. ዘእግዝእትነ: <locus target="#15r">fol.
                                 15r</locus> (hand a). ዘመድኃኔ፡ ዓለም: <locus target="#20v">fol.
                                 20v</locus> (hand a). &lt;...&gt;: <locus target="#21v">fol.
                                 21v</locus>. ዘሥራኅ: <locus target="#23v">fol. 23v</locus> (hand a).
                              ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#29r">fol. 29r</locus> (hand a). ዘሙታን: <locus target="#32v">fol. 32v</locus> (hand a).</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Title of the work and supplication mentioning the names of the donors are written in a crude secondary hand on 
                              <locus target="#35v">fol.  35v</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc> - Doodles in fols. 35v, 37r, 37v, 38r, 38v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two leather boards (possibly re-used, cp. the holes on
                           the outer edges).
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="leather"/>
